text: TFW you take the a.m. off work for a "by 10:30am" @FedExHelp overnite delivery, now it's 1pm & you're taking the afternoon off too apparently & all they will tell you "it's on the truck," then blame flooding 2 hrs away for why the truck disappeared in the 2 miles btwn them & you

@VZWSupport I mean, I can, but I've already talked to Verizon once and FedEx twice today & all they can tell me is that "it's on the truck" though @FedExHelp has no way of knowing where any of their vehicles are, but that they might call me in the next 2/4/7000 hours if the driver checks in.

@VZWSupport I tried chat and there was no response. I just sat on hold. I have been sitting around for 6 1/2 hours waiting for this delivery, which I paid extra to have delivered YESTERDAY by 10:30am, and neither @VZWSupport nor @FedExHelp can help me. (1/2)

Condolences to @FedExHelp because clearly your driver has driven into a black hole and died or fallen through a wormhole into another dimension. I'm sure you'd agree that otherwise it would be ludicrous if @FedEx had no way of contacting a driver in a 7-hour period "just 'cause."
